WEBVTT

00:00:56.203 --> 00:00:58.622
EPISODE 10

00:01:28.110 --> 00:01:29.278
RECIPIENT: HAN SEO-YUL

00:01:51.008 --> 00:01:52.051
STAFF JU HYUN-SU

00:02:59.660 --> 00:03:01.578
Damn it, this bastard is so careless.

00:03:02.162 --> 00:03:03.956
I told him not to order stuff
to this place.

00:03:35.696 --> 00:03:36.613
Seol-ah.

00:03:37.489 --> 00:03:38.782
Why are you here?

00:03:39.742 --> 00:03:41.035
What about you?

00:03:42.661 --> 00:03:44.121
The man you just saw…

00:03:45.706 --> 00:03:46.623
is Ju Hyun-su.

00:03:47.791 --> 00:03:49.126
The bastard who killed my sister.

00:03:52.212 --> 00:03:53.797
Why were you following him?

00:03:53.881 --> 00:03:55.466
I wasn't following him.

00:03:56.133 --> 00:03:58.635
I came to find Chair Kim's property
registered under a borrowed name.

00:04:01.096 --> 00:04:02.973
Ju Hyun-su spotted
in Chair Kim's building?

00:04:06.560 --> 00:04:08.520
Is there a connection between them?

00:04:09.271 --> 00:04:11.732
I can only speculate at this point.

00:04:12.566 --> 00:04:14.109
We can't talk here.

00:04:14.193 --> 00:04:15.903
-Let's go somewhere else and--
-No.

00:04:17.071 --> 00:04:18.405
I don't have anything more to say.

00:04:19.239 --> 00:04:21.116
That's all I know.

00:04:27.456 --> 00:04:29.083
Are you feeling better?

00:04:33.420 --> 00:04:35.089
Are you eating well?

00:04:38.092 --> 00:04:40.969
Take care of yourself too, Woo-seok.

00:05:09.581 --> 00:05:11.792
The man you just saw is Ju Hyun-su.

00:05:11.875 --> 00:05:13.043
The bastard who killed my sister.

00:05:14.086 --> 00:05:16.213
Ju Hyun-su spotted
in Chair Kim's building?

00:05:17.965 --> 00:05:19.758
Is there a connection between them?

00:05:38.652 --> 00:05:40.320
What are you thinking about?

00:05:40.404 --> 00:05:42.489
It's just an overnight trip.

00:05:42.573 --> 00:05:44.408
I didn't lie like my friends did

00:05:44.491 --> 00:05:46.201
and was honest about
taking a trip with my boyfriend.

00:05:46.285 --> 00:05:48.370
Jeez, when did you grow up?

00:05:48.453 --> 00:05:50.080
You always treat me like a child.

00:05:50.831 --> 00:05:52.416
I think I'll get married before you.

00:05:53.041 --> 00:05:54.459
Ms. Cha Woo-hee.

00:05:55.627 --> 00:05:57.754
Marriage already? Control yourself.

00:05:57.838 --> 00:05:59.298
Drop me off over there.

00:06:04.720 --> 00:06:06.221
Call me when you get to Busan.

00:06:06.305 --> 00:06:07.556
Eat that, okay?

00:06:07.639 --> 00:06:09.391
-Be careful.
-Okay.

00:06:28.327 --> 00:06:29.203
Hey, Woo-hee.

00:06:29.703 --> 00:06:30.913
Is this Mr. Cha Woo-seok?

00:06:32.164 --> 00:06:34.708
I'm Woo-hee's boyfriend.

00:06:36.793 --> 00:06:40.172
Ms. Cha, who was in the passenger seat,
wasn't wearing a seat belt,

00:06:40.255 --> 00:06:43.383
and traces of sleeping pills
were found in her blood.

00:06:43.467 --> 00:06:45.886
Furthermore, at the suggestion
of the defendant, Ju Hyun-su,

00:06:45.969 --> 00:06:48.555
she took out a life insurance policy
worth 300 million won,

00:06:48.639 --> 00:06:50.265
naming him as the beneficiary.

00:06:50.349 --> 00:06:51.725
POLICYHOLDER: CHA WOO-HEE
BENEFICIARY: JU HYUN-SU

00:06:51.808 --> 00:06:53.936
Although the circumstances are suspicious,

00:06:54.019 --> 00:06:57.397
there's no objective evidence
that the accident was intentional

00:06:57.940 --> 00:06:59.942
with respect to the charges
of murder and fraud.

00:07:01.902 --> 00:07:03.570
The defendant, Ju Hyun-su,

00:07:03.654 --> 00:07:05.530
is hereby sentenced to one year in prison.

00:07:05.614 --> 00:07:07.532
The sentence
will be suspended for two years

00:07:07.616 --> 00:07:10.035
from the date this ruling becomes final.

00:07:31.181 --> 00:07:32.808
There are traces showing
the artworks were moved.

00:07:42.359 --> 00:07:43.360
Why would Ju Hyun-su do that?

00:08:08.844 --> 00:08:10.637
You stated that you saw Han Seol-ah

00:08:10.721 --> 00:08:14.057
coming down from the rooftop
on the night of Kim Yun-ji's death.

00:08:15.058 --> 00:08:18.687
But you're the only one without an alibi
at the time Kim Yun-ji fell.

00:08:20.856 --> 00:08:23.775
Are you framing Han Seol-ah
after killing Kim Yun-ji yourself?

00:08:23.859 --> 00:08:26.403
You even disguised your voice
and called in a tip.

00:08:26.486 --> 00:08:27.779
That's not true!

00:08:27.863 --> 00:08:29.990
I didn't kill anyone.

00:08:30.073 --> 00:08:30.949
Look here.

00:08:31.700 --> 00:08:35.662
I don't think you realize
what charges brought you here.

00:08:36.496 --> 00:08:39.082
I followed Han Seol-ah
to see what she was up to.

00:09:01.730 --> 00:09:03.398
I thought it was suspicious
that they left together,

00:09:04.107 --> 00:09:05.859
so I tried to keep an eye on her,

00:09:06.818 --> 00:09:07.944
but I lost her again.

00:09:09.988 --> 00:09:10.822
"Again"?

00:09:17.746 --> 00:09:18.580
Fine.

00:09:19.790 --> 00:09:21.166
I was the one…

00:09:23.418 --> 00:09:25.837
who recorded the video
the night Ms. Kim died.

00:09:30.008 --> 00:09:31.301
What are you trying to say?

00:09:32.469 --> 00:09:33.470
I'm curious.

00:09:34.388 --> 00:09:37.474
If the secret you've been hiding
is out in the open,

00:09:38.183 --> 00:09:39.810
would you still be so composed?

00:09:46.566 --> 00:09:49.194
Why did you keep following Han Seol-ah?

00:09:49.986 --> 00:09:51.363
Why?

00:09:51.947 --> 00:09:54.074
Because the police can't arrest her.

00:09:54.157 --> 00:09:55.575
Because you people can't do your job!

00:09:55.659 --> 00:09:58.703
Because even now,
you have the wrong person!

00:09:58.787 --> 00:10:01.206
Why are you doing this to me?

00:10:01.289 --> 00:10:03.166
What did I do that was so wrong?

00:10:05.335 --> 00:10:06.920
I didn't kill anyone.

00:10:22.436 --> 00:10:25.439
So you're saying you didn't
supply champagne that day, right?

00:10:27.023 --> 00:10:27.858
Yes.

00:10:28.567 --> 00:10:32.070
Chair Kim said she'd prepare it herself
because it was a VIP event.

00:10:32.654 --> 00:10:33.780
Chair Kim of Royal Auction?

00:10:34.364 --> 00:10:35.490
Yes.

00:10:35.574 --> 00:10:38.910
I didn't supply the champagne
that caused Mr. Paek to collapse.

00:10:40.620 --> 00:10:42.247
Then why were you at the event?

00:10:44.374 --> 00:10:46.626
I got an invitation from Seol-ah

00:10:46.710 --> 00:10:48.336
and went through the proper channels.

00:10:48.420 --> 00:10:50.547
No, I'm asking why you went there.

00:10:51.047 --> 00:10:52.591
What was the purpose?

00:10:56.511 --> 00:10:58.013
I thought I could meet…

00:11:00.098 --> 00:11:01.766
a decent man.

00:11:04.352 --> 00:11:05.854
To be honest, I like parties.

00:11:06.771 --> 00:11:09.900
I don't get many chances
to wear pretty dresses in Korea.

00:11:10.525 --> 00:11:12.235
You weren't even on the guest list

00:11:12.319 --> 00:11:13.820
for the event
held on the night of Kim Yun-ji's death.

00:11:14.321 --> 00:11:16.072
Did you go there just to wear a dress?

00:11:16.990 --> 00:11:19.075
I swear I didn't do much.

00:11:20.285 --> 00:11:21.286
So you did do something.

00:11:21.369 --> 00:11:22.913
No, I didn't!

00:11:22.996 --> 00:11:25.415
Kim Yun-ji was acting really strange.

00:11:26.416 --> 00:11:28.251
Ms. Han only drinks decaf, right?

00:11:29.336 --> 00:11:30.378
Okay.

00:11:33.840 --> 00:11:36.051
-Here's your coffee.
-Thank you.

00:11:36.134 --> 00:11:38.094
DECAF

00:11:49.189 --> 00:11:50.941
It's mint tea.

00:11:52.025 --> 00:11:52.984
Thank you.

00:12:04.204 --> 00:12:05.372
What are you doing?

00:12:05.872 --> 00:12:07.457
What are you, a stalker?

00:12:08.291 --> 00:12:09.751
Are you jealous of the chief auctioneer?

00:12:10.502 --> 00:12:12.337
If I catch you messing with Seol-ah again,

00:12:13.004 --> 00:12:14.673
I'll kill you myself.

00:12:22.097 --> 00:12:23.473
I was just trying to scare her.

00:12:24.766 --> 00:12:26.393
I had no idea that would happen.

00:12:27.477 --> 00:12:30.522
Then where were you
at the time of Kim Yun-ji's fall?

00:12:30.605 --> 00:12:32.190
At the party.

00:12:32.274 --> 00:12:34.234
I watched in shock with the other guests.

00:12:34.317 --> 00:12:36.069
Ask anyone who was there.

00:12:50.375 --> 00:12:52.627
Jeez, that was terrifying.

00:12:53.628 --> 00:12:55.964
How did Seol-ah get through this?

00:12:56.047 --> 00:12:57.215
My goodness.

00:12:57.299 --> 00:12:59.259
Unbelievable.

00:13:00.302 --> 00:13:02.679
I've never had a consignor die before.

00:13:03.263 --> 00:13:05.515
This final year of misfortune
is making quite a commotion.

00:13:06.641 --> 00:13:08.935
What legal issues do we need to go over?

00:13:09.978 --> 00:13:11.980
The consignment contract specifies

00:13:12.063 --> 00:13:13.898
that Royal Auction has an obligation

00:13:13.982 --> 00:13:18.236
to keep the painting safe
until the owner appears.

00:13:18.320 --> 00:13:19.613
So you're saying

00:13:19.696 --> 00:13:22.616
it's okay for us to keep the painting
until the owner shows up, right?

00:13:22.699 --> 00:13:23.825
Yes, ma'am.

00:13:23.908 --> 00:13:25.827
It's likely this case
will end up in court,

00:13:25.910 --> 00:13:27.621
so it could take quite a while.

00:13:28.246 --> 00:13:29.497
I see.

00:13:30.540 --> 00:13:31.541
Chair Kim.

00:13:32.125 --> 00:13:33.251
Please look at this.

00:13:34.002 --> 00:13:36.254
This was in Ms. Han's possession.

00:13:40.342 --> 00:13:41.760
LIST OF CHAIR KIM'S PROPERTIES
REGISTERED UNDER BORROWED NAMES

00:13:43.637 --> 00:13:44.971
You've got a lot of time on your hands.

00:13:45.055 --> 00:13:48.016
I gave you an opportunity,
and you're still looking into her?

00:13:48.099 --> 00:13:50.310
If you can't find a replacement
for the Stiller,

00:13:50.393 --> 00:13:52.228
you're going to Busan too. Got it?

00:13:52.812 --> 00:13:53.938
But Chair Kim…

00:13:54.856 --> 00:13:55.732
Yes, ma'am.

00:13:59.486 --> 00:14:02.030
RECIPIENT: HAN SEO-YUL

00:14:02.113 --> 00:14:02.989
This is their base of operations.

00:14:03.573 --> 00:14:05.158
It seems that Han Seo-yul,
the one behind the Taemyung accident,

00:14:05.241 --> 00:14:06.910
is living with Ju Hyun-su.

00:14:08.203 --> 00:14:10.246
As expected,
your instincts are on the mark.

00:14:10.830 --> 00:14:13.958
You said it followed the same pattern
as your sister's accident.

00:14:15.293 --> 00:14:18.338
So these bastards were all in it together.

00:14:19.214 --> 00:14:20.215
What about the paintings?

00:14:21.633 --> 00:14:24.302
There were traces showing the paintings
had been moved into a vacant building.

00:14:24.886 --> 00:14:26.805
And from there, they moved them
to a more concealed location.

00:14:27.764 --> 00:14:31.309
At least we secured the Stiller
before it also disappeared.

00:14:32.519 --> 00:14:34.270
What's going to happen to it

00:14:34.354 --> 00:14:36.022
now that the owner is dead?

00:14:36.106 --> 00:14:37.899
It'll go through the inheritance process.

00:14:39.567 --> 00:14:41.653
I checked with the policyholder's lawyer,

00:14:42.320 --> 00:14:45.407
and a beneficiary had already been named
in the event of his death.

00:14:46.533 --> 00:14:49.452
There's no way Han Seol-ah
could be involved in this too, right?

00:14:54.207 --> 00:14:55.333
This can't be real.

00:15:06.970 --> 00:15:09.472
ARTICLE 1
(TESTATOR AND BENEFICIARY INFORMATION)

00:15:12.016 --> 00:15:14.144
TESTATOR: PAEK JUN-BEOM
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

00:15:25.572 --> 00:15:27.949
Why do you hate Han Seol-ah so much?

00:15:28.742 --> 00:15:29.826
I liked her

00:15:30.785 --> 00:15:31.828
when I was young.

00:15:33.788 --> 00:15:35.582
Since I was six years old,

00:15:36.207 --> 00:15:38.251
my brother has been my whole world.

00:15:50.680 --> 00:15:51.806
Do Eun-hyuk, get up.

00:16:03.276 --> 00:16:04.194
Get up.

00:16:14.287 --> 00:16:15.705
-Eun-hye.
-Yes?

00:16:15.789 --> 00:16:17.874
Go tell your brother to come eat.

00:16:18.458 --> 00:16:19.292
Okay.

00:16:43.066 --> 00:16:45.068
All his life, my brother has had eyes

00:16:46.069 --> 00:16:47.445
only for Han Seol-ah.

00:16:48.446 --> 00:16:50.073
It's fine that he loves her

00:16:50.156 --> 00:16:52.700
more than his own sister

00:16:52.784 --> 00:16:54.410
as long as he's happy.

00:16:56.621 --> 00:16:57.455
But…

00:16:59.040 --> 00:17:01.251
it made me furious to see him
constantly being used

00:17:01.751 --> 00:17:04.504
and getting nothing in return.

00:17:07.423 --> 00:17:08.842
I thought if I exposed who she really was,

00:17:08.925 --> 00:17:10.802
he'd give up on her.

00:17:11.511 --> 00:17:13.847
I wanted him to see
that she wasn't a victim of bad luck

00:17:14.973 --> 00:17:16.516
but an evil witch who kills people.

00:17:18.434 --> 00:17:20.687
So you're saying Han Seol-ah is a witch.

00:17:24.148 --> 00:17:26.317
And yet your brother

00:17:26.401 --> 00:17:28.862
would still do anything for her.

00:17:33.533 --> 00:17:34.617
Eun-hye.

00:17:36.119 --> 00:17:37.370
Eun-hyuk.

00:17:38.162 --> 00:17:39.247
Get up.

00:17:39.330 --> 00:17:40.164
Let's go.

00:17:59.058 --> 00:18:01.936
Why aren't you saying anything?

00:18:03.229 --> 00:18:05.857
Why aren't you getting mad or scolding me?

00:18:11.905 --> 00:18:13.114
Let's go eat.

00:18:13.197 --> 00:18:14.240
What do you want?

00:18:16.576 --> 00:18:18.578
Shouldn't I eat tofu or something?

00:18:19.162 --> 00:18:20.246
You weren't released from prison.

00:18:21.706 --> 00:18:23.458
You were just brought in for questioning.

00:18:24.292 --> 00:18:27.211
I just don't want to come back
to a police station again.

00:18:27.295 --> 00:18:28.838
And I'm scared

00:18:28.922 --> 00:18:30.590
even though I didn't do anything wrong.

00:18:37.347 --> 00:18:38.640
I'm sorry.

00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:43.811
I'm sorry for everything.

00:18:45.563 --> 00:18:46.397
Then…

00:18:47.982 --> 00:18:49.233
treat me to grilled barbecue.

00:18:49.317 --> 00:18:51.694
I want premium Korean beef, not pork.

00:18:53.780 --> 00:18:54.614
Let's go.

00:19:04.040 --> 00:19:04.999
Did you really go

00:19:06.292 --> 00:19:07.669
to all of those addresses?

00:19:08.836 --> 00:19:10.129
The properties on Chair Kim's list?

00:19:12.215 --> 00:19:13.758
I'm working my way down the list.

00:19:15.259 --> 00:19:16.928
How's Eun-hye doing?

00:19:17.011 --> 00:19:19.013
Apparently, she cried her eyes out
at the police station.

00:19:20.515 --> 00:19:22.225
I was nervous myself,

00:19:22.308 --> 00:19:23.643
so you can imagine how she felt.

00:19:24.394 --> 00:19:25.436
It's all my fault.

00:19:26.813 --> 00:19:29.816
She may be an adult,
but she's still a kid on the inside.

00:19:30.400 --> 00:19:32.026
I've been insensitive.

00:19:32.902 --> 00:19:34.862
Right, don't scold her too much.

00:19:35.571 --> 00:19:37.198
She did it for you.

00:19:37.281 --> 00:19:38.533
She's right.

00:19:38.616 --> 00:19:40.326
When you love someone,
you want to protect them.

00:19:41.953 --> 00:19:44.580
I totally went off on Kim Yun-ji
the night she died.

00:19:45.623 --> 00:19:46.457
You did?

00:19:47.333 --> 00:19:49.585
It looked like she was giving you
a hard time at work,

00:19:50.211 --> 00:19:52.171
so I was waiting for my chance
to tell her off.

00:19:52.255 --> 00:19:54.507
But I shouldn't have stepped in like that.

00:19:55.091 --> 00:19:56.217
I'm sorry, Seol-ah.

00:19:56.801 --> 00:19:58.553
I've been meaning to tell you,

00:19:59.303 --> 00:20:00.722
but I just couldn't bring myself to.

00:20:02.056 --> 00:20:03.933
Why did you do that?

00:20:04.934 --> 00:20:06.102
I don't know.

00:20:07.895 --> 00:20:08.896
Thank you.

00:20:11.649 --> 00:20:12.775
It's comforting to know

00:20:13.526 --> 00:20:15.528
that I have people who stand up for me.

00:20:16.779 --> 00:20:18.531
Remember how you two always fought for me

00:20:18.614 --> 00:20:21.200
when we were young?

00:20:21.784 --> 00:20:24.245
Whenever kids bad-mouthed or bullied me,

00:20:25.371 --> 00:20:27.707
Eun-hyuk would beat them up,
and you'd humiliate them.

00:20:29.667 --> 00:20:31.919
I'm sorry. I should've thanked you sooner.

00:20:33.212 --> 00:20:36.174
Hey, why are you saying that
all of a sudden?

00:20:36.257 --> 00:20:37.925
Now I feel even more guilty.

00:20:42.096 --> 00:20:43.765
Don't cry. You'll ruin your makeup.

00:20:45.475 --> 00:20:47.685
I just wanted to protect you.

00:20:48.686 --> 00:20:49.562
You know that, right?

00:20:57.779 --> 00:21:00.239
CHA WOO-SEOK

00:21:35.942 --> 00:21:39.987
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be directed to voicemail…

00:21:45.284 --> 00:21:46.661
Did you really mean it?

00:21:50.414 --> 00:21:53.668
Do you really want me
to stop focusing on you?

00:21:55.253 --> 00:21:56.462
When we were young…

00:21:58.798 --> 00:22:01.342
I thought we'd go to college together

00:22:02.552 --> 00:22:04.887
and grow up to be special to each other.

00:22:06.556 --> 00:22:07.640
But

00:22:08.224 --> 00:22:11.477
seeing you keep your distance

00:22:12.061 --> 00:22:15.898
made me realize
you only wanted me as a friend.

00:22:16.566 --> 00:22:17.692
I wondered

00:22:18.526 --> 00:22:20.236
if my past was too much of a burden
even for you,

00:22:21.612 --> 00:22:23.865
then who could I ever be with?

00:22:24.448 --> 00:22:25.783
It wasn't like that.

00:22:26.742 --> 00:22:28.828
Do you know why I dated Su-ho?

00:22:30.079 --> 00:22:31.998
It was because
he had even less than I did.

00:22:32.540 --> 00:22:35.960
Even someone like me
could feel pity for him,

00:22:36.544 --> 00:22:40.089
and I couldn't just turn away
knowing how much he needed me.

00:22:42.300 --> 00:22:45.386
So you chose Lee Su-ho over me?

00:22:46.262 --> 00:22:47.889
I didn't want to lose you.

00:22:49.223 --> 00:22:52.143
And it was easier for me
to date someone who liked me.

00:22:53.436 --> 00:22:54.395
I was just a coward.

00:22:55.646 --> 00:22:56.981
Did you go out with those other men

00:22:57.899 --> 00:22:59.400
just because they liked you?

00:23:00.151 --> 00:23:01.777
I didn't want to be alone,

00:23:01.861 --> 00:23:03.738
and I wanted a family of my own.

00:23:05.615 --> 00:23:06.532
I thought

00:23:07.783 --> 00:23:09.619
I was a strong person,

00:23:10.661 --> 00:23:12.121
but I guess I was wrong.

00:23:13.497 --> 00:23:15.374
Don't try so hard to be strong.

00:23:16.792 --> 00:23:18.044
Just be yourself

00:23:19.712 --> 00:23:20.922
and continue living.

00:23:22.298 --> 00:23:24.675
Lee Su-ho died twice because of me.

00:23:25.843 --> 00:23:28.846
You made the right decision not to become

00:23:30.014 --> 00:23:31.515
one of my men.

00:23:32.141 --> 00:23:33.643
Seol-ah, that's not…

00:23:51.327 --> 00:23:53.079
GANGHA POLICE STATION

00:23:53.663 --> 00:23:56.123
Chair Kim prepared the champagne
on her own?

00:23:56.207 --> 00:23:57.792
What's her connection to Han Seol-ah?

00:23:57.875 --> 00:23:59.293
Is she just her boss?

00:23:59.877 --> 00:24:01.671
Paek Jun-beom was their VIP client,

00:24:01.754 --> 00:24:04.465
so Chair Kim purposely put Han Seol-ah
in charge of him.

00:24:05.132 --> 00:24:07.301
Check if there's an insurance policy
involved in this case too.

00:24:07.802 --> 00:24:09.595
Let's see if it follows the pattern
of the previous victims.

00:24:10.304 --> 00:24:12.306
I have my suspicions about Do Eun-hyuk.

00:24:13.307 --> 00:24:15.226
But his alibi checked out last time.

00:24:16.102 --> 00:24:17.687
I didn't think he was an accomplice

00:24:17.770 --> 00:24:20.022
because he was here
when Woo-seok got into that accident.

00:24:20.106 --> 00:24:22.984
But Lee Su-ho was behind that,
so it had nothing to do with Do Eun-hyuk.

00:24:24.360 --> 00:24:26.362
When we interrogated Do Eun-hye,

00:24:26.445 --> 00:24:29.198
it sounded like Do Eun-hyuk
would do anything for Han Seol-ah.

00:24:31.617 --> 00:24:34.453
Track his movements
on the day Lee Su-ho died.

00:24:45.214 --> 00:24:46.632
Are you working right now?

00:24:48.551 --> 00:24:50.845
Wow, how do you take photos like this?

00:24:51.846 --> 00:24:53.931
Do you go underwater with the models?

00:24:54.682 --> 00:24:56.767
I go to an underwater studio.

00:24:56.851 --> 00:24:58.936
Sometimes, I'll go to a freediving center

00:25:00.104 --> 00:25:02.148
or head out to a river or the ocean.

00:25:04.900 --> 00:25:06.569
They look amazing,

00:25:07.361 --> 00:25:08.571
but isn't it dangerous?

00:25:09.572 --> 00:25:11.490
You must be good at scuba diving.

00:25:13.326 --> 00:25:14.952
I haven't had any serious accidents yet.

00:25:17.079 --> 00:25:17.913
Anyway,

00:25:18.622 --> 00:25:19.707
what brings you here?

00:25:20.541 --> 00:25:22.877
You were the photographer at the event

00:25:23.544 --> 00:25:25.379
on the day Paek Jun-beom died, right?

00:25:25.963 --> 00:25:26.797
Of course.

00:25:27.673 --> 00:25:28.591
You saw Paek Jun-beom…

00:25:29.467 --> 00:25:32.636
I mean, you saw Lee Su-ho
collapse too, right?

00:25:32.720 --> 00:25:33.763
Everyone saw that.

00:25:37.558 --> 00:25:39.727
Where did you go after the event?

00:25:42.396 --> 00:25:43.731
I went to Cheongun,

00:25:43.814 --> 00:25:45.399
where I own a private studio.

00:25:46.359 --> 00:25:48.652
I thought you usually went there
on weekends.

00:25:48.736 --> 00:25:52.490
But you went all the way there
on a weekday at such a late hour?

00:25:52.990 --> 00:25:55.409
I had an urgent project to wrap up.

00:25:57.536 --> 00:25:59.997
Can you prove that you were in Cheongun?

00:26:02.500 --> 00:26:04.043
How would you like me to prove it?

00:26:04.126 --> 00:26:06.712
Your dashcam footage should do.

00:26:07.880 --> 00:26:10.007
There's CCTV in front of the studio.

00:26:10.091 --> 00:26:11.342
Would you like me to check that too?

00:26:11.425 --> 00:26:14.095
Submitting both would be great.

00:26:14.678 --> 00:26:15.513
Sure thing.

00:26:32.738 --> 00:26:34.657
We have a 100 million phone bid.

00:26:35.324 --> 00:26:36.826
The highest bid so far is 100 million won.

00:26:37.326 --> 00:26:40.371
Anyone at 105 million?

00:26:40.454 --> 00:26:42.206
We have 105 million.

00:26:42.289 --> 00:26:44.083
We received the highest bid on the floor.

00:26:44.792 --> 00:26:47.044
Anyone at 110 million?

00:26:47.128 --> 00:26:48.045
At 110 million--

00:26:48.129 --> 00:26:49.338
I withdraw my bid.

00:26:50.840 --> 00:26:51.966
I changed my mind.

00:26:52.049 --> 00:26:53.259
Excuse me?

00:26:56.178 --> 00:26:57.555
You lost your momentum.

00:26:58.055 --> 00:27:01.225
All eyes are on your mouth,
so what will you do?

00:27:01.767 --> 00:27:05.604
An auctioneer
doesn't just call out numbers.

00:27:05.688 --> 00:27:08.858
They make you believe
the value of the artwork.

00:27:08.941 --> 00:27:11.610
No matter how hectic it gets,
you have to stay focused.

00:27:13.821 --> 00:27:15.322
You have to believe in yourself.

00:27:16.282 --> 00:27:18.868
The bid withdrawal has been confirmed.

00:27:18.951 --> 00:27:20.327
The highest bid so far

00:27:20.411 --> 00:27:22.496
is the phone bid of 100 million.

00:27:22.580 --> 00:27:25.374
Let me ask again. Anyone at 105 million?

00:27:25.458 --> 00:27:27.710
If there are no more bids,

00:27:27.793 --> 00:27:30.379
I'll call it three times
before closing the bidding.

00:27:31.464 --> 00:27:32.465
105 million?

00:27:33.048 --> 00:27:33.966
105 million?

00:27:34.049 --> 00:27:36.760
Anyone at 105 million?

00:27:37.595 --> 00:27:38.429
100 million.

00:27:39.346 --> 00:27:40.473
Sold.

00:29:17.319 --> 00:29:18.362
Hello?

00:29:18.445 --> 00:29:19.363
Ms. Han,

00:29:19.446 --> 00:29:21.490
I'm calling from the secretary's office
at Your Home.

00:29:23.409 --> 00:29:24.535
How can I help you?

00:29:25.411 --> 00:29:27.538
I'm calling
regarding an inheritance matter.

00:29:31.750 --> 00:29:32.751
YOUR HOME LEGAL TEAM
ATTORNEY KIM JUN-SEONG

00:29:32.835 --> 00:29:35.462
I'm the attorney handling
the late Mr. Paek Jun-beom's will.

00:29:37.631 --> 00:29:40.634
He left something to you.

00:29:41.218 --> 00:29:42.511
Me?

00:29:42.595 --> 00:29:46.849
You've been bequeathed
an Emil Stiller piece.

00:29:47.349 --> 00:29:49.602
Prior to the auction, he took out a policy

00:29:49.685 --> 00:29:53.689
and designated you as the beneficiary
in the event of his death.

00:29:54.315 --> 00:29:57.693
I've heard nothing about this,
nor have I agreed to it.

00:29:57.776 --> 00:30:00.529
A bequest doesn't require
the recipient's consent.

00:30:02.448 --> 00:30:05.367
It appears he wanted to keep it a secret.

00:30:06.493 --> 00:30:10.122
Mr. Paek had been in poor health due to
the aftereffects of the accident in Syria,

00:30:10.205 --> 00:30:13.083
so he had taken precautions
for any unexpected situations.

00:30:21.216 --> 00:30:23.677
Will this really be
Ms. Han's last auction?

00:30:23.761 --> 00:30:25.262
She's being sent to the Busan branch,

00:30:25.346 --> 00:30:26.889
which basically means she's fired.

00:30:27.848 --> 00:30:29.975
I didn't realize that's what it meant.

00:30:30.059 --> 00:30:32.561
Does this make any sense to you, Tae-seok?

00:30:32.645 --> 00:30:33.687
Of course not.

00:30:33.771 --> 00:30:35.189
How can Sang-mi take the main podium?

00:30:36.440 --> 00:30:39.735
We're nearly equal in experience,
yet I have to call her chief auctioneer.

00:30:40.235 --> 00:30:42.780
I did all the hard work,
so why is she getting promoted?

00:30:43.656 --> 00:30:45.574
Hard work?

00:30:46.158 --> 00:30:47.493
I'm not sure about that.

00:30:47.993 --> 00:30:48.827
What did you say?

00:30:59.296 --> 00:31:01.215
Are you still seeing Han Seol-ah?

00:31:02.591 --> 00:31:04.468
It seems like she's about to get fired
from Royal Auction.

00:31:06.929 --> 00:31:08.430
I'm here for work.

00:31:09.973 --> 00:31:11.100
Great excuse.

00:31:12.059 --> 00:31:13.560
Any progress on the investigation?

00:31:16.313 --> 00:31:17.523
So you're not going to
tell me anything now?

00:31:18.524 --> 00:31:20.484
You don't exactly
tell me everything either.

00:31:22.903 --> 00:31:24.071
Let's talk later.

00:31:24.154 --> 00:31:25.072
About what?

00:31:45.175 --> 00:31:46.760
I'm sorry for showing up unannounced.

00:31:49.638 --> 00:31:50.931
But you wouldn't answer my calls.

00:31:52.015 --> 00:31:54.601
Should I guess why you're here?

00:31:58.522 --> 00:31:59.648
The Stiller.

00:32:24.882 --> 00:32:25.883
Go ahead and ask.

00:32:27.676 --> 00:32:29.928
You came to ask me questions, right?

00:32:30.888 --> 00:32:33.974
You want to know why Su-ho left me
such a high-value painting,

00:32:34.057 --> 00:32:36.477
whether I knew about it,

00:32:37.436 --> 00:32:39.146
and whether I manipulated him
into doing it.

00:32:42.107 --> 00:32:44.318
It's unlikely
that it'll become your property

00:32:45.068 --> 00:32:46.653
because it depends on whether it's viewed

00:32:47.654 --> 00:32:49.406
as a bequest from Paek Jun-beom

00:32:50.449 --> 00:32:51.784
or from Lee Su-ho.

00:32:54.578 --> 00:32:56.413
Is that what you came to tell me?

00:32:57.581 --> 00:33:00.459
That the Stiller won't be mine?

00:33:03.086 --> 00:33:04.296
I came because I missed you.

00:33:10.010 --> 00:33:11.053
And because I'm worried.

00:33:22.147 --> 00:33:24.149
It's a special clause
in the event of a death,

00:33:24.233 --> 00:33:25.484
so the police don't know yet.

00:33:25.567 --> 00:33:27.027
We can't stall for too long,

00:33:27.110 --> 00:33:29.238
but it can buy us some time
until the culprit is revealed--

00:33:29.321 --> 00:33:30.239
There's no need for that.

00:33:31.073 --> 00:33:33.242
Give them all the information they want.

00:33:33.325 --> 00:33:36.036
Then you'll become
their prime suspect again.

00:33:37.037 --> 00:33:38.205
Maybe…

00:33:39.498 --> 00:33:41.458
that's what Su-ho wanted all along.

00:33:42.793 --> 00:33:45.879
I don't believe he left me that painting

00:33:45.963 --> 00:33:47.840
purely for my sake.

00:33:49.842 --> 00:33:50.968
Let me remind you

00:33:52.219 --> 00:33:53.720
that you're in danger.

00:33:54.304 --> 00:33:57.057
I was never the one the culprit was after.

00:33:58.058 --> 00:33:59.560
It was always the man by my side.

00:34:10.320 --> 00:34:11.363
Then protect me.

00:34:13.365 --> 00:34:14.908
Don't push me away out of fear.

00:34:16.243 --> 00:34:17.452
Don't run away.

00:34:20.163 --> 00:34:21.498
Stay right by my side…

00:34:24.251 --> 00:34:25.419
and protect me.

00:35:00.454 --> 00:35:01.705
We need to talk.

00:35:07.544 --> 00:35:10.047
LIST OF CHAIR KIM'S PROPERTIES
REGISTERED UNDER BORROWED NAMES

00:35:10.631 --> 00:35:12.633
I was about to head out to see you.

00:35:13.634 --> 00:35:14.468
TERRACE DE VILLA

00:35:14.551 --> 00:35:16.678
I was going through Chair Kim's properties
registered under borrowed names

00:35:16.762 --> 00:35:19.348
to find out where the Taemyung paintings
might be hidden.

00:35:21.850 --> 00:35:23.477
HYUN-SU'S FRUIT

00:35:25.437 --> 00:35:26.355
Ju Hyun-su

00:35:27.439 --> 00:35:28.774
is Chair Kim's henchman.

00:35:30.442 --> 00:35:33.654
I've seen him come and go from her suite.

00:35:33.737 --> 00:35:35.948
I thought you should know.

00:35:37.074 --> 00:35:38.784
We've been after the same person.

00:35:39.743 --> 00:35:41.536
If we recover the Taemyung pieces,

00:35:41.620 --> 00:35:45.123
we'll find out everything
Chair Kim and Ju Hyun-su have done.

00:35:45.874 --> 00:35:46.917
And…

00:35:47.501 --> 00:35:48.627
we can set right

00:35:49.670 --> 00:35:51.505
the injustices your sister suffered.

00:35:57.928 --> 00:36:01.014
There were traces showing the paintings
had been moved to a storage space here.

00:36:01.098 --> 00:36:03.725
I think they used it as a warehouse
when they switched the paintings.

00:36:04.518 --> 00:36:07.896
Chair Kim handles risky business elsewhere

00:36:07.980 --> 00:36:09.606
and moves the pieces
to the secret storage vault

00:36:09.690 --> 00:36:11.024
once it's safe.

00:36:12.734 --> 00:36:14.319
Then the Taemyung paintings…

00:36:16.655 --> 00:36:18.991
Among all the storage facilities
the company has contracts with,

00:36:19.491 --> 00:36:21.827
there's one place
the employees can't access.

00:36:22.452 --> 00:36:25.205
They blocked it off
for Chair Kim's personal use.

00:36:26.081 --> 00:36:28.125
The storage facility
where the accident happened.

00:36:30.961 --> 00:36:32.212
The one where we ran into Paek Jun-beom?

00:36:58.989 --> 00:37:02.159
Why did you invite me
to such an expensive place?

00:37:03.577 --> 00:37:05.704
What I wanted was one of your meals.

00:37:09.207 --> 00:37:11.084
An SIU investigator is involved.

00:37:12.127 --> 00:37:15.881
Ms. Han is working with him,
and they're coming after me.

00:37:22.304 --> 00:37:23.722
What are you going to do
about the Taemyung accident?

00:37:27.976 --> 00:37:29.227
Don't worry about that.

00:37:29.311 --> 00:37:31.354
There's nothing they can do,
even if they suspect something.

00:37:32.314 --> 00:37:33.899
Our guy is clean,
and there's no hard evidence.

00:37:33.982 --> 00:37:36.234
What if they find the paintings?

00:37:36.318 --> 00:37:38.111
Don't you know it's all over

00:37:38.695 --> 00:37:40.322
the second that happens?

00:37:41.907 --> 00:37:44.785
They're in a safe place, so don't worry.

00:37:48.121 --> 00:37:49.331
It's too risky to keep them outside.

00:37:49.915 --> 00:37:51.750
Move them to my storage vault.

00:37:53.627 --> 00:37:54.461
Okay.

00:38:39.840 --> 00:38:42.926
FELIX STORAGE

00:39:26.386 --> 00:39:29.264
The artwork storage space
just became available,

00:39:29.347 --> 00:39:31.391
so you can sign a new contract with us.

00:39:35.312 --> 00:39:37.397
Are you saying there were paintings here
until just a moment ago?

00:39:37.981 --> 00:39:39.900
Yes, someone canceled their contract.

00:39:40.775 --> 00:39:43.695
Are there any other storage rooms
dedicated to artwork?

00:39:43.778 --> 00:39:46.656
No, this is the only one.

00:39:47.407 --> 00:39:49.618
Were there issues
with the facility or security?

00:39:50.202 --> 00:39:51.203
I believe they were taken in a hurry

00:39:51.286 --> 00:39:53.079
due to the contract holder's
personal reasons.

00:40:00.420 --> 00:40:01.588
I'm certain those paintings

00:40:02.547 --> 00:40:04.299
were the Taemyung pieces.

00:40:06.343 --> 00:40:07.719
That truck we saw earlier…

00:40:14.684 --> 00:40:16.228
I should've checked it.

00:40:16.311 --> 00:40:18.563
Then there's only one possibility left.

00:40:18.647 --> 00:40:20.607
How much time do we have
until the last auction?

00:40:21.316 --> 00:40:22.400
One week.

00:40:23.526 --> 00:40:25.111
That's all the time we have

00:40:25.820 --> 00:40:27.405
to get into Chair Kim's
secret storage vault.

00:41:10.282 --> 00:41:12.284
I heard you're being pressured
to leave the company.

00:41:13.243 --> 00:41:15.662
It's understandable
from Chair Kim's perspective.

00:41:16.288 --> 00:41:18.999
No one likes an employee
who frequents the police station.

00:41:20.500 --> 00:41:22.752
It couldn't have been easy
to hide your feelings

00:41:24.296 --> 00:41:26.047
while working alongside an enemy.

00:41:27.424 --> 00:41:28.466
There were moments

00:41:30.176 --> 00:41:31.761
when I faltered…

00:41:33.805 --> 00:41:37.309
because I couldn't fully hate someone
as much as I should have.

00:41:48.570 --> 00:41:50.447
I've seen many cases like that
in this job.

00:41:51.489 --> 00:41:52.907
Mothers who blind their own children

00:41:53.491 --> 00:41:55.577
to collect insurance payouts,

00:41:56.703 --> 00:41:58.872
and kids who try to protect those monsters
just because they're their moms.

00:42:00.165 --> 00:42:02.042
I'm sure your feelings toward Chair Kim

00:42:03.376 --> 00:42:04.461
are similar to that.

00:42:07.339 --> 00:42:08.381
Woo-seok,

00:42:09.382 --> 00:42:11.384
how do you know everything?

00:42:13.803 --> 00:42:15.263
Because I was a survivor too.

00:42:52.550 --> 00:42:53.968
Jeez, what took you so long?

00:42:54.052 --> 00:42:55.095
I'm starving, you know?

00:42:55.178 --> 00:42:57.347
It's not like I could just eat whatever
at someone else's place.

00:43:03.770 --> 00:43:04.771
Wow.

00:43:04.854 --> 00:43:05.897
What a perfect shot.

00:43:06.898 --> 00:43:08.066
Very nice.

00:43:08.149 --> 00:43:10.193
You two look good together.

00:43:18.159 --> 00:43:19.077
Take a look.

00:43:19.160 --> 00:43:21.746
This is the subcontractor that worked with
the architect who designed Royal Auction.

00:43:21.830 --> 00:43:24.582
Companies like this
tend to have weak security.

00:43:24.666 --> 00:43:29.170
The Royal Auction building
was completed on July 15, 2017.

00:43:31.047 --> 00:43:34.759
I think this contains the blueprint files
exchanged from 2016 to 2017.

00:43:44.227 --> 00:43:46.521
ROYAL AUCTION_13F (CHAIRMAN'S SUITE).PDF

00:43:46.604 --> 00:43:48.273
AHN ARCHITECTS

00:43:50.608 --> 00:43:51.901
Found it.

00:43:55.363 --> 00:43:56.489
Just as I thought.

00:43:57.449 --> 00:44:00.243
It's in the space behind the kitchen wall
in Chair Kim's suite.

00:44:01.411 --> 00:44:02.620
That's a pretty large space.

00:44:03.204 --> 00:44:04.873
Is there really
a secret storage vault there?

00:44:05.623 --> 00:44:07.333
It's close, easy to manage,

00:44:07.417 --> 00:44:10.044
and more importantly,
there are no CCTVs on this floor.

00:44:18.178 --> 00:44:20.221
We're not thinking of
infiltrating this place, are we?

00:44:40.658 --> 00:44:42.619
CORNERSTONE
HERE BEGINS A NEW ERA OF ART

00:44:42.702 --> 00:44:45.497
Chair Kim always uses the same passcode.

00:44:50.043 --> 00:44:52.086
It's 170715.

00:44:53.505 --> 00:44:55.256
COMPLETED: JULY 15, 2017
BUILDING OWNER: KIM SUN-AE

00:45:03.890 --> 00:45:05.642
Congratulations, Ms. Han!

00:45:06.267 --> 00:45:09.854
My goodness.

00:45:11.231 --> 00:45:13.608
It seems Mr. Paek left you a huge gift.

00:45:14.984 --> 00:45:18.154
I hear the Stiller is yours now.

00:45:20.907 --> 00:45:23.117
I have no intention of accepting it.

00:45:23.701 --> 00:45:25.078
Are you insane?

00:45:25.161 --> 00:45:27.372
The person who died
wasn't the real Paek Jun-beom.

00:45:27.455 --> 00:45:29.123
He was an impersonator.

00:45:29.707 --> 00:45:31.084
It wasn't his property,

00:45:31.167 --> 00:45:33.169
so he had no right to leave it to anyone.

00:45:33.253 --> 00:45:34.420
Don't worry about that.

00:45:34.504 --> 00:45:36.339
I've already looked into
the legal side of things.

00:45:36.422 --> 00:45:39.676
Legally, the chance of you getting it

00:45:39.759 --> 00:45:40.593
is very high.

00:45:40.677 --> 00:45:42.845
If it doesn't work out,
we'll file a lawsuit.

00:45:42.929 --> 00:45:44.556
I'll cover all the costs.

00:45:46.849 --> 00:45:48.476
That's a big investment to make

00:45:48.560 --> 00:45:50.728
in an employee you're about to let go.

00:45:51.312 --> 00:45:52.355
Let go?

00:45:53.064 --> 00:45:54.774
I told you to take a break
at the Busan branch.

00:45:54.857 --> 00:45:56.317
I never told you to leave the company.

00:45:56.401 --> 00:45:58.778
Seeing how things are,
you don't have to go to Busan.

00:46:00.613 --> 00:46:02.657
Your father

00:46:02.740 --> 00:46:05.994
can finally rest in peace,

00:46:06.077 --> 00:46:08.288
now that his daughter's life
is looking up.

00:46:12.458 --> 00:46:15.461
The main lot for the upcoming auction
hasn't been decided yet.

00:46:15.545 --> 00:46:17.338
Did you review the list I sent you?

00:46:26.556 --> 00:46:28.850
Artist Song Hwan-ju's posthumous work.

00:46:31.352 --> 00:46:34.272
It's their final piece
that was never revealed.

00:46:34.897 --> 00:46:38.818
This will cause quite a sensation
once it's made public.

00:46:39.944 --> 00:46:41.070
How did you…

00:46:41.154 --> 00:46:44.407
Any replacement for the Stiller
has to have just as much impact.

00:46:45.325 --> 00:46:49.787
This is the most valuable card
I have up my sleeve.

00:46:52.081 --> 00:46:52.999
That's wonderful.

00:46:54.292 --> 00:46:55.293
A piece like this

00:46:55.376 --> 00:46:57.712
could attract the same attention
as a Stiller would.

00:46:59.339 --> 00:47:02.800
You're giving me quite a grand gift
for my last auction.

00:47:07.680 --> 00:47:09.682
I'm giving you a chance…

00:47:11.559 --> 00:47:13.811
and you still insist
this is your last time?

00:47:24.947 --> 00:47:28.159
INSURANCE POLICY
NAME: PAEK JUN-BEOM

00:47:29.744 --> 00:47:31.454
GROUNDS FOR RESCISSION OF THE POLICY

00:47:31.537 --> 00:47:32.872
CONSIGNOR: PAEK JUN-BEOM
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

00:47:33.790 --> 00:47:34.666
"Bequest"?

00:47:35.375 --> 00:47:39.212
It's a special clause stating that,
in the event of Paek Jun-beom's death,

00:47:39.295 --> 00:47:42.006
Han Seol-ah is bequeathed the Stiller
as well as any resulting payout.

00:47:42.090 --> 00:47:42.924
What?

00:47:43.007 --> 00:47:45.510
The estimated winning bid is valued
at over 15 billion won.

00:47:45.593 --> 00:47:47.679
Are you saying
all that goes to Han Seol-ah?

00:47:48.596 --> 00:47:50.098
It's a powerful motive for murder.

00:47:51.974 --> 00:47:55.061
If Han Seol-ah was behind all this,

00:47:55.144 --> 00:47:56.813
she might've changed her MO.

00:47:56.896 --> 00:47:58.898
All the men have died so far,

00:47:58.981 --> 00:48:00.983
but she hasn't succeeded
in collecting the payouts.

00:48:01.984 --> 00:48:02.819
However,

00:48:03.569 --> 00:48:05.279
the painting is something
she can definitely get.

00:48:05.905 --> 00:48:07.782
And the stakes get higher.

00:48:07.865 --> 00:48:10.702
But Paek Jun-beom was actually Lee Su-ho.

00:48:10.785 --> 00:48:12.203
Can he even make a bequest?

00:48:12.286 --> 00:48:14.747
I actually looked into it,
and it's pretty complicated.

00:48:14.831 --> 00:48:16.708
He did live under
Paek Jun-beom's identity,

00:48:16.791 --> 00:48:19.085
but it can still be considered
Lee Su-ho's asset,

00:48:19.168 --> 00:48:21.003
so there's room for legal dispute.

00:48:21.087 --> 00:48:22.588
Then this could end up in court.

00:48:24.382 --> 00:48:27.260
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

00:49:02.086 --> 00:49:04.964
I put the GPS tracker on Chair Kim's car.

00:49:05.548 --> 00:49:06.924
Dr. Shin will be monitoring.

00:49:13.806 --> 00:49:15.224
Are you sure you'll be okay?

00:49:16.267 --> 00:49:17.143
Maybe I should--

00:49:17.226 --> 00:49:20.146
In the worst-case scenario,
someone will have to carry out Plan B.

00:49:20.730 --> 00:49:23.983
It's okay if I get caught
because I'm leaving the company anyway.

00:49:24.066 --> 00:49:26.611
But if you get caught,
there's no way to handle it.

00:49:28.654 --> 00:49:30.615
Get out right away
once you've recorded the evidence, okay?

00:49:44.337 --> 00:49:45.338
NETWORK CONNECTION
CANCEL / CONNECT

00:49:45.421 --> 00:49:48.716
CONNECTING…

00:50:26.712 --> 00:50:28.756
Chair Kim is heading home.

00:50:28.840 --> 00:50:30.341
Get ready in case
the security team shows up,

00:50:30.424 --> 00:50:31.717
and keep an eye on the entrance.

00:51:43.831 --> 00:51:44.874
I'm in front of the storage vault.

00:51:54.467 --> 00:51:56.552
Passcode, 170715.

00:52:16.739 --> 00:52:17.907
I'm going in.

00:52:18.491 --> 00:52:19.325
Be careful.

00:52:38.761 --> 00:52:39.845
I'm inside.

00:52:47.186 --> 00:52:48.062
Woo-seok?

00:52:48.145 --> 00:52:49.230
Seol-ah?

00:52:50.314 --> 00:52:51.440
Seol-ah.

00:52:57.321 --> 00:52:58.948
UNSTABLE CONNECTION, CHECK NETWORK
TRY AGAIN

00:53:04.328 --> 00:53:05.162
ACCESS GRANTED

00:53:05.246 --> 00:53:06.080
DOOR SECURED

00:53:06.163 --> 00:53:08.040
Is this an error or what?

00:53:27.810 --> 00:53:30.229
Vanished Sensation by Fabien Leclerc

00:53:30.312 --> 00:53:33.149
has been sold to Chairman Park Min-cheol
of Taemyung Group.

00:53:36.235 --> 00:53:37.987
FIRE BREAKS OUT ON A TRUCK TRANSPORTING
TAEMYUNG CULTURAL FOUNDATION ART

00:54:02.053 --> 00:54:03.137
Turn the car around.

00:54:10.770 --> 00:54:12.271
What the heck? Why is she going back?

00:54:12.980 --> 00:54:13.898
What's going on?

00:54:13.981 --> 00:54:15.900
Chair Kim's car
is heading back to the company.

00:54:15.983 --> 00:54:17.401
Ms. Han has to get out of there.

00:55:18.796 --> 00:55:21.006
I can't get the eyes to look like Mom's.

00:55:21.966 --> 00:55:23.592
Let's take a look.

00:55:26.011 --> 00:55:28.347
It's not that
they don't look like her eyes.

00:55:28.889 --> 00:55:30.516
Her eyes are just complicated.

00:55:31.392 --> 00:55:32.852
Look into them.

00:55:33.435 --> 00:55:36.730
They're full of stories of her life.

00:55:37.898 --> 00:55:40.860
What does that mean?

00:55:40.943 --> 00:55:42.611
It's a compliment.

00:55:42.695 --> 00:55:46.115
You're starting to see the person,
not just the drawing.

00:55:46.198 --> 00:55:48.242
I want to draw as well as you do.

00:55:48.826 --> 00:55:51.078
Skills improve quickly as you learn.

00:55:51.162 --> 00:55:51.996
But you see,

00:55:52.746 --> 00:55:55.249
not everyone can put their heart into it.

00:55:55.332 --> 00:55:58.002
But you have that in you, Seol-ah.

00:55:58.669 --> 00:55:59.962
I'm more proud of that.

00:56:00.546 --> 00:56:01.547
Really?

00:56:01.630 --> 00:56:02.756
Of course. You're my daughter.

00:56:02.840 --> 00:56:05.676
Goodness, you two are so alike.

00:56:06.552 --> 00:56:08.345
Looks like we'll have another artist
in the family.

00:56:08.929 --> 00:56:10.222
What's wrong with that?

00:56:10.806 --> 00:56:12.766
Seol-ah, don't become an artist.

00:56:12.850 --> 00:56:14.101
Be a doctor instead.

00:56:14.727 --> 00:56:17.688
Seol-ah will become
a famous artist, right?

00:56:18.355 --> 00:56:19.565
Yeah.

00:56:25.196 --> 00:56:26.155
Listen.

00:56:26.780 --> 00:56:28.199
If this becomes your posthumous piece,

00:56:28.282 --> 00:56:29.867
-I'll make sure it sells for a high price.
-No!

00:56:29.950 --> 00:56:31.035
Please!

00:56:31.118 --> 00:56:32.828
I'm begging you!

00:56:37.458 --> 00:56:38.792
No!

00:56:38.876 --> 00:56:41.003
Please let me keep that one!

00:56:41.086 --> 00:56:42.796
No!

00:57:12.618 --> 00:57:13.869
I see her.

00:57:13.953 --> 00:57:15.746
What should I do? Ram into her?

00:57:15.829 --> 00:57:17.373
She's coming. What do I do?

00:57:17.456 --> 00:57:19.792
-Make up your mind!
-I'm going in.

00:57:25.381 --> 00:57:27.299
Hurry up! She's pulling in!

00:58:12.177 --> 00:58:13.178
You're getting off work late.

00:58:13.262 --> 00:58:14.638
There's a shoot tomorrow,

00:58:14.722 --> 00:58:16.056
so I had to prepare before I left.

00:58:29.069 --> 00:58:30.279
The exit passcode is different.

00:59:55.989 --> 00:59:58.075
Take care of that bastard quietly first.

00:59:58.700 --> 01:00:01.286
It's not enough,
but they'll show up in front of me soon.

01:00:01.370 --> 01:00:04.456
No, I won't use you as bait.

01:00:04.540 --> 01:00:07.668
I'm the only one who can approach them
without raising suspicion.

01:00:07.751 --> 01:00:08.585
Get her.

01:00:08.669 --> 01:00:10.796
Don't you dare touch anything!
Hey, Han Seol-ah!

01:00:10.879 --> 01:00:12.756
This isn't over

01:00:13.340 --> 01:00:14.675
until we catch the killer.

01:00:14.758 --> 01:00:16.051
It's been a while.

01:00:16.135 --> 01:00:19.096
It'll be your neck on the line.

01:00:19.179 --> 01:00:20.264
It's your fault.

01:00:20.848 --> 01:00:23.767
I guess we'll just have to wait and see

01:00:24.351 --> 01:00:25.727
whose neck is on the line.

01:00:27.938 --> 01:00:29.940
Subtitle: Jenny Kim